ng</h3>\r\nDog Trainer U.S. highly customizes our service dog training programs personalized to the individual seeking assistance or the job the dog will do.\r\n\r\nDog Trainer U.S. is committed to assisting those individuals thru the entire process of selecting the appropriate service dog and training (including basic, advanced obedience and task training to mitigate the disability).  Also, full public access training including education about city, state, &amp; federal laws impacting service dogs in the United States as well as laws governing service dogs in other countries.\r\nDog Trainer U.S. is pleased to have, one of only six, Internationally Certified Service Dog Trainers in the world, having met the stringent requirements by the International Association of Service Dog Professionals (IACP) for this elite certification, mentoring all of our Volunteer trainers.  Additionally, Kristi has been on the IACP SD Committee since its inception, has previously chaired the committee, and is actively assisting with the trainer certification, public access testing process and is on the International Project workgroup.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row full_width=\"stretch_row_content_no_spaces\" content_placement=\"middle\" css=\".vc_custom_1589379210140{background-color: #f7f7f7 !important;}\"][vc_column el_class=\"container\" css=\".vc_custom_1589379268227{margin-top: 10px !important;}\"][vc_row_inner content_placement=\"middle\" el_class=\"container\" css=\".vc_custom_1589379113374{margin-top: 15px !important;}\"][vc_column_inner width=\"1/2\" css=\".vc_custom_1589380120326{margin-top: 40px !important;padding-right: 30px !important;}\"][vc_column_text]\r\n<h3 class=\"text-right\">Therapy Dog</h3>\r\nDog Trainer U.S.’s Therapy dog training programs are designed to train your dog and you to provide a service for others. This includes basic &amp; advanced obedience, house manners, public access and training behaviors to assist you with performing this service. 